title: For Sale/Trade:  Genuine pre-ban h&k 91 battle rifle
postcontent: Up for sale / trade is a genuine pre-ban 1981 Heckler & Koch 91 battle rifle. These are incredibly rare and hard to find. As a pre-ban it is one of a very limited number of H&KS in the country which are eligible to be converted to full auto assuming you're willing to jump through the legal hoops and pay the cost to complete the conversion. What makes this rifle even more rare is that it comes with a factory installed ambi safety (almost unheard of) and also a shell deflector. These were never included in standard production, so the fact that they are factory OEM parts makes this rifle a real one of a kind. This rifle had been professionally assessed by a well respected Knoxville gunsmith and is certified as all original parts and also in 90-95% condition. The rifle also has a collapsible stock rather than the fixed stock as well as fully operational sights peeps for zeroing at 100, 200, 300 and 400 yards. Book value on this rifle easily exceeds $3,000 and I have turned down a cash offer in that amount. This .308 is a true battle rifle and kicks like a mule - this is not a plinker or a good choice as al first rifle. Experienced shooters will appreciate this rifle, inexperienced shooters will regret the purchase / trade. If you have a serious interest in working a sale / trade on this rifle I would be happy for you to have it assessed by your own gunsmith prior to the transaction.

postcontent:
I have a variety of indoor range brass for sale. They have been fired and still have the primers. You will need to clean and deprime them yourself. I pick out pieces that are Berdan primed or are bent or cracked to the point that they cannot be reloaded. However, some of these may get into the bags. I weigh out an extra 10 pieces for every 500 to ensure you have quality pieces. These are all brass or nickel coated brass--no aluminum or steel! These are mixed headstamp and the .45s have NOT been sorted for primer size (I would estimate 5-10% small primer).
